            "description": "",
            "details": "<p><em>Baḥr-i Fārs</em><span> (Persian Gulf): It is a sea that emerges from the northern side of the </span><em>Baḥr-i Hind</em><span> (Indian Ocean). To the east of </span><em>Mekrāntīz</em><span> (Makran coast region), at the source of the </span><em>Baḥr-i Fārs</em><span>, it appears visibly like a mouth (</span><em>dehān</em><span>). Likewise, the city of </span><em>‘Ummān</em><span> (Oman) is seen on the western side of this sea, and it too is discernible at its mouth, that is, its strait. From there it extends, running along the </span><em>‘Ummān</em><span> (Oman) coast, and from </span><em>‘Abbādān</em><span> (Abadan, Iran) to </span><em>Mehrūbān</em><span> (Mahrūbān, near modern Bushehr). Then it passes to </span><em>Sīnīz</em><span> (modern Bushehr/Old Siniz) and stretches southward until it reaches </span><em>Ḫayyābe</em><span> (Khabbah / Khaybah). From there it proceeds to </span><em>Seyfü’l-baḥr</em><span> (“the Sword of the Sea,” Fars coast), and to its east is </span><em>Sīrāf</em><span> (Siraf, Iran). From that point, it continues along broken mountain ranges and high desert passes and hills, and then, moving further east, it winds around to </span><em>Ḥıṣn Ibn ‘Ammāre</em><span> (Hisn Ibn ‘Ammāra) and reaches </span><em>Hürmüz</em><span> (Hormuz), which is the port of </span><em>Kirmān</em><span> (Kerman). After that, it stretches toward the southeastern direction, reaching the Makran coast and </span><em>Ḳaṣṣatīz</em><span>. [translation]</span></p>",
            "end": 1599,
